---
import BaseLayout from "../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
import PageHeader from "../components/PageHeader.astro";
import { SITE } from "../lib/site";
---

<BaseLayout
  title="About"
  description="What the Twilight Biathlon is, how the format works, and why we run at night."
>
  <PageHeader
    eyebrow="// About"
    title="The original nighttime run-and-gun biathlon."
  />

  <section class="mx-auto max-w-3xl px-4 py-16 sm:px-6 lg:px-8">
    <div class="prose-content space-y-6 text-lg text-[var(--color-text)]/90 leading-relaxed">
      <p>
        The Twilight Biathlon is a timed 5K run-and-shoot competition held at
        night on unlit terrain at {SITE.venue.name} in {SITE.venue.city},
        {SITE.venue.state}. Competitors run a two-lap course through Oklahoma
        fields and woods, engaging four live-fire shooting stages along the
        route.
      </p>

      <p>
        Four divisions cover the field: <strong>2Gun</strong> and
        <strong>PCC</strong> run Saturday night on white light, while
        <strong>NV 2Gun</strong> and <strong>NV PCC</strong> run Friday night on
        night vision only with no white light permitted anywhere on the course.
      </p>

      <p>
        Scoring is time-based. Your final score is the combined total of your
        four shooting stage times plus your course run time. Lowest score wins.
      </p>

      <h2 class="!mt-12 font-[family-name:var(--font-display)] text-3xl font-bold uppercase">
        Running since 2018
      </h2>
      <p>
        Twilight Biathlon has run twice a year — spring and fall — since 2018.
        The format, the NV/WL split, and the 5-minute individual release schedule
        are the original template for this type of event.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>

